===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|non|nōn|lang=ang}}, from a Germanic borrowing of classical {{etyl|la}} {{term|nona|nōna|ninth hour|lang=la}} (short for {{term|nona|nōna|lang=la}} {{term|hora|hōra|lang=la}}), feminine of {{term|nonus|nōnus|ninth|lang=la}}.  Cognate with Flemish {{term|noen|lang=vls}}, obsolete German {{term|Non|lang=de}}, Norwegian {{term|non|lang=no}}.

